OL,3,CThe last of the neon sign makers
OL,4,Cfighting to save the craft
OL,6,FOnce you couldn't walk down a city
OL,7,Fcentre street without being surrounded
OL,8,Fby the glow of neon signs - from the
OL,9,Ffamous lights of Piccadilly Circus and
OL,10,Fthe Blackpool Illuminations, to the
OL,11,F'DINER' sign hanging over the door of
OL,12,Fevery local late night cafe.
OL,14,FBut those sights could soon become a
OL,15,Fthing of the past - according to one
OL,16,Fof the country's last neon sign makers
OL,17,F- who says more needs to be done to
OL,18,Fsave the craft for future generations.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/12
