OL,3,CThe last of the neon sign makers
OL,4,Cfighting to save the craft
OL,6,FIn the 20th century there were
OL,7,Fhundreds of people employed in making
OL,8,Fneon signs for art and advertising all
OL,9,Faround the country - now there are
OL,10,Fless than 30.
OL,12,F"There's a real chance that neon sign
OL,13,Fmaking will die out" says Catherine
OL,14,FSpink, who runs Neon Creations with
OL,15,Fher husband Tony from a workshop in
OL,16,FBolton.
OL,18,FShe added: "It's on the Heritage Craft
OL,19,FAssociation's red list of endangered
OL,20,Fcrafts in the UK.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/12
