OL,3,CThe last of the neon sign makers
OL,4,Cfighting to save the craft
OL,6,F"There are currently no trainees
OL,7,Flearning the craft because that relies
OL,8,Fon businesses being able to take
OL,9,Fpeople on to train them up. If the
OL,10,Fdemand isn't there for neon, business
OL,11,Faren't able to afford the costs of a
OL,12,Ftrainee.
OL,14,F"So eventually what could happen is
OL,15,Fthat the glass benders that we've got
OL,16,Fnow, as they get older and retire from
OL,17,Fthe industry, there will be nobody
OL,18,Fthere to replace them"
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/12
