OL,3,CThe last of the neon sign makers
OL,4,Cfighting to save the craft
OL,6,FThe method of neon sign making hasn't
OL,7,Fchanged since 1898 - glass tubes are
OL,8,Fheated, bent and blown into shape
OL,9,Fbefore being filled with neon and
OL,10,Fother inert gas. When electricity is
OL,11,Fapplied, the tubes shine with that
OL,12,Ffamous neon glow.
OL,14,FIt means traditional neon signs are
OL,15,Fall handmade and time consuming
OL,16,Fcreations - and in recent years
OL,17,Fbusinesses have struggled to compete
OL,18,Fwith mass-produced, LED reproductions
OL,19,Fwhich are allowed to market themselves
OL,20,Fas "neon".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/12
