OL,3,CThe last of the neon sign makers
OL,4,Cfighting to save the craft
OL,6,FGlass bender Tony Spink says the
OL,7,FGovernment needs to do more to protect
OL,8,F"neon" as a trademark term, giving it
OL,9,Fa clear definition and legal
OL,10,Fprotections, like that given to Harris
OL,11,FTweed or Cornish pasties.
OL,13,F"I've got nothing against LED lights",
OL,14,FTony explains, "but they're a very
OL,15,Fdifferent product, and the labelling
OL,16,Fof these kind of signs as neon is
OL,17,Fhaving a real effect on our business.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/12
