OL,3,CThe last of the neon sign makers
OL,4,Cfighting to save the craft
OL,6,FSpeaking in a parliamentary debate,
OL,7,Fthe Minister for the Creative
OL,8,FIndustries said the Government had
OL,9,Fheard the case being made for neon
OL,10,Fsignage. "Protecting neon is not about
OL,11,Fnostalgia. It is about supporting
OL,12,Flivelihoods, unlocking tourism, and
OL,13,Fgiving our public spaces character."
OL,15,FChris Bryant MP added: "I hear the
OL,16,Fcall for consumer transparency and
OL,17,Fgreater support`whether through
OL,18,Fplanning protections, trademarking or
OL,19,Fcultural preservation funding.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/12
